gomodel:SYNGO_2004  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In figures 3 and 5, the authors use immunogold electron microscopy to localize AP180 in rat synapses. Figure 3 is synapses from CA1 neurons and figure 5 is synapses from cerebellar granule cells on Purkinje neurons.\n\n6/12/2017 Pim\n- The plasma membrane term of the postsynapse was selected as inferred canonical site of action for clathrin coat recruitment.. Experimental description: From results, \"Two rats were processed for postembedding immunogold labelling...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2004" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

